description:
Aimed Research is currently the most affordable high-speed imaging solution in America, utilizing top-tier cameras and flash units for research, development and engineering. Aimed Research's knowledge-base and skills were acquired directly from the defense industry and we therefore provide specialized services for ballistic tests. Our cameras and flash units are available for rental to select customers or with an operator for on-site service to any customer. 

Aimed Research is supported by professional talent that has designed programmable munitions, firing control systems and other electronics, though Aimed Research is not currently a manufacturer of any products. Aimed Research is open to work in-part or in-whole with your organization to provide accelerated results for your product development.

description:
「ぼくたちにとって動いて見えるテレビ映像ですら、昆虫から見ればカタカタとした 動きにしか見えない。時間とはいったい何だろうか？」
時間を引きのばして昆虫の世界を見れば、そこには驚異の世界が見えてくる。私たちがスムーズに見えるテレビもカマキリが見たらコマ落としの映像にしかみえないだろう。（なにしろ獲物を捕る速度はわずか1/20秒である）
それほど昆虫の動きは早い。普通のビデオカメラではとらえきれない昆虫の動きや行動を高速度ビデオカメラを用いて時間を10倍から40倍に引き延ばして撮影している。
今では動画はビデオカメラだけでなくスチールカメラでも撮れる。このコーナーでは撮りだめた数々の動画や新しくスチールカメラで撮っている最新動画などを掲載していくことにする。

description:
Welcome to JimLiElevators: My name is Jim and I am an elevator photographer based in central Texas. I have always loved elevators when I was a kid. Been filming since 2005. I present to you videos of elevators that are both vintage and modern. Not only that I film elevators, but I've also been interested into trains as well. I'll occasionally upload animated elevators because I've had a lot of fun making them. So with that said, I hope you enjoy your visit to my channel.

Thanks so much for your loyal viewership. I take pride in keeping this channel clean for all ages. I am also a born Christian, so I want to keep it pleasing to Jesus as well! “For God so loved the world that he gave his only son that believes in him shall not perish but have eternal life. John 3:16."

I'm also thankful to Andrew Reams (DieselDucy) who's the deepest inspiration towards me to start this channel. That said, make sure you subscribe. Thanks and have a great day! :D

description:
The Splash Lab seeks to unravel the physical mechanisms of fluid behaviors, through a novel 3D volumetric measurement method known as Synthetic Aperture Imaging and imbedded instrumentation (e.g., accelerometers, etc). We experimentally analyze fluid systems such as fluid-structure interactions, multi-phase flows, and free surface phenomena.  Currently, we are funded by the Office of Naval Research and the National Science Foundation to improve our imaging techniques and elucidate topics from skipping balls to projectile water entry.  Most of our projects are fun and interesting as we try to make them accessible to the public through high quality photography and video production!
For more information
Website: http://splashlab.byu.edu
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/byusplashlab
Twitter: https://twitter.com/BYUSplashLab
Instagram: BYUSplashLab

description:
Mike Orazzi is a New England photographer and newspaper photojournalist based in Connecticut. He owns too many Jeeps and chainsaws, like mud, working outside and of course photography. The photography pays the bills. 
I use Nikon photography gear active cameras that I use are from the Nikon Z9, Nikon D850, Nikon D500, Nikon D3, I still sometimes use a D7100 or A D300.
For glass I have a 400f2.8, 300 f2.8, 200-400 f4, 70-200f2.8, wide glass doesn't get used much.
For videos I have been having a lot of fun with a Canon Vixia HF G70. 

Everything else you see here spends all of my money and then some. Check here for random videos of tractors, Jeeps, something diesel, news, and whatever else we happen to be doing. #compacttractor #photographer #photography #nikonz9 #z9 #outdoors #canon  Use the playlists to easier navigation.

Cílem naší firmy je poskytovat kvalitní služby firmám v oblasti energetiky a průmyslu. Společnost "TMV SS" je nejen výhradním obchodním, ale i servisním zastoupením. Samozřejmostí je předávání zakoupené techniky přímo u uživatele, zaškolení uživatelů, manuály v českém jazyce a následná podpora zákazníků formou konzultací, seminářů a firemního "hotline". description: The world-famous Cincinnati Zoo & Botanical Garden is committed to inspiring visitors to care about wildlife and wild places. It was voted the #1 Best Zoo and the #1 Best Botanical Garden by USA TODAY and has also received rave reviews from Child Magazine, Parents Magazine, Newsweek, and TripAdvisor. Nearly 2 million people visit the Zoo’s award-winning habitats and gardens annually. The Zoo, an accredited member of the Association of Zoos & Aquariums since 1978, is internationally known for its success in the protection and propagation of endangered animals and plants and engages in research and conservation projects worldwide. Known as the #GreenestZooInAmerica, the Zoo is doing its part to conserve natural resources that are critical to saving wildlife and habitats and is committed to greening its daily operations and reducing its impact on the environment with rain gardens, recycled building materials, solar panels and more. The Cincinnati Zoo is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization.

Next to high speed passenger trains I also have some videos about cargo and freight trains  available from time to time: So feel free to zap through my videos or playlists! Most of my videos were taken in Cologne and Aachen and in the closer area arround these cities.

Most of my videos were taken with a smartphone: I started in 2012 with an Apple iPhone 4 and you can see, that it misses optical image stabilization. All newer videos taken with later iPhone models therefore are more steady due to the improved camera optics.

description:
Welcome to my channel, LAXSPOTTER97. My name is Julian and as you can see I am a big aviation fan and I have many other hobbies and interests. I hope you can enjoy my videos as much as I do.

I post videos when I can. I am in school and have 2 jobs so time isnt exactly abundant. However most of the time I will try to upload something every other day.
Recently I moved to Portland Oregon and will be bringing you videos from the Pacific Northwest region, however I will be making trips to LAX hopefully several times a year to keep my channel title relevant.
I will also try to film some scenes from local airshows but that will only be 1 to 4 times a year.

Thank you, 
Enjoy


Planes I have been on-
Delta 767-300ER
Delta 757 200
Delta Connection E175
LTU A330-200
United 777-200
United 737-800
United 737-900ER
Southwest 737-700
Alaska A320

description:
Ronivaldo Passos Sampaio é um engenheiro de Machine Learning na Secretaria da Fazenda do Ceará (Sefaz/CE), com formação em Mecatrônica e Computação.  Ele possui certificações como Investigador Forense, incluindo CHFI e DSCP. Sua atuação na Célula de Inteligência de Dados da Sefaz/CE busca otimizar processos fiscais e tributários no estado. Em 2022, Ronivaldo recebeu menção honrosa no Prêmio Tributare pelo desenvolvimento de uma ferramenta com Inteligência Artificial que auxilia na emissão de Certificados de Não-Similaridade, tornando o processo mais ágil e eficiente.  Além disso, ele liderou a Comunidade Arduino Day Fortaleza por oito anos, organizando eventos anuais com cerca de 1.200 participantes, e é um ativo palestrante em eventos de Python, Arduino e Inteligência Artificial.

Em seu canal no YouTube, Ronivaldo compartilha conteúdos relacionados à tecnologia, inteligência artificial e desenvolvimento de chatbots, incluindo tutoriais sobre ChatGPT e Arduino e Awin.

description:
Victor Marx is a high risk humanitarian with successful missions to Iraq, Syria, North Africa and Southeast Asia – many times in non-permissive and high threat environments, helping orphans and widows.

Severely abused and tortured as a child, by the time he graduated from high school, his lifestyle was filled with drugs, fights and theft. The discipline of military life and faith in God helped him recover from his traumatic childhood and empowers him to help others. Today, Victor focuses his attention to the plights of those affected by ISIS, troubled juvenile offenders, and supporting military personnel from all branches including the special operations community.

A husband of 30 years, a father to five and a proud grandfather, Victor has learned and teaches his approach to build successful relationships while excelling professionally.

description: This is Steve Son's YouTube page.  Our research group at Purdue University is primarily interested in a wide range of fundamental energy and energetic materials (propellants, explosives, and pyrotechnics) research areas.  We focus on state-of-the-art dynamic experimentation and creating novel reactive materials.  We develop or apply the most advanced diagnostics often applied in harsh reacting environments to develop improved understanding and characterization.  We also seek to develop tailored disruptive energetic materials with unique properties.  Ultimately our research aims to improve the performance, safety, or toxicity of energetic materials. We also have interest in energy topics, including coal combustion and hydrogen storage.

description:
MIKROTRON - a brand of SVS-Vistek GmbH

The MIKROTRON brand is internationally known in the machine vision market for small, particularly robust High-Speed cameras that are used in industrial and scientific applications as well as in sports, advertising and nature filming.

SVS-Vistek GmbH has exceptional know-how in industrial image processing as an innovative manufacturer of high-quality industrial CCD and CMOS cameras for more than 35 years. 
We develop and produce a wide range of standard cameras as well as cameras with the highest resolutions and highest speeds, above-average image quality and all relevant interfaces in our own clean rooms at our headquarters in Gilching near Munich: Quality Made in Germany! 
With subsidiaries in the USA and Japan as well as a large partner network, we can advise, support and serve customers of many markets worldwide.

We believe that quality is important to both customers and us, so we never compromise on quality. It wasn’t easy in the beginning when people tended to bargain on the price. description:
View supplemental videos from our published reviews. 

Annual Reviews was founded in 1932 as a nonprofit organization dedicated to bringing the most comprehensive scientific review literature to its readers. Annual Reviews journals operate as a high quality filter, prioritizing and synthesizing the primary research literature in 46 different disciplines for the Biomedical, Life, Physical, and Social Sciences, including Economics. All topics for review are selected by an editorial committee comprised of the most distinguished scholars of the discipline. Annual Reviews articles are written by leading scholars to help researchers and students navigate the vast amount of primary research literature that is available to them. As a result, each article is its own search engine, providing a gateway to the most significant literature within a topic.

description:
We’re a weird hybrid studio/production company that, at our core, strives to bring you fun, genuine entertainment, whether it’s TV shows, feature films, short films, live streams, tutorials, or anything in-between. We pride ourselves on making better stories than you’d expect and with more heart than you’d imagine.

We started with Video Game High School, a three-season, full-length, award-winning independent web series. It was named #1 Web Series of 2013 by Variety, nominated for a Producer’s Guild Award for Outstanding Digital Series in 2014 and 2015, and won Streamy Awards for Direction, Ensemble Cast, and Action/Sci-Fi Series. Soon after, we partnered with Lionsgate, which resulted in the 2015 behind-the-scenes documentary series RocketJump: The Show on Hulu, our upcoming sci-fi anthology show Dimension 404, and a whole bunch more awesome stuff to come.

Hello & Welcome! I'm Gordon, known as Trackwerk (formerly Orion V 9967 here on YouTube)! Please feel free to take a look at my Transportation videos created as far back as 2010! Many now retired Transit Vehicles are featured in my videos! I appreciate every person's support - if you have knowledge to share when watching my videos please feel free to comment! 

Much more content is in the works of being uploaded soon!
Some works include:
 • Station by Station featuring different angles of every station along the line for the following projects: R32 J/Z, R160 A, D via Culver, R62A 4 in Brooklyn and more! 
 • Rare and unusual trains and buses such as nightly Garbage Trains or special reroutes
 • Soon to be or recently retired trains or buses (many videos dating back to 2011 to be uploaded)
 • Tours of interesting and mostly unknown places mostly within NYC with much info

Make sure to Subscribe and Stay Tuned for upcoming future content! 
Follow me on IG @trackwerk

Relax and Enjoy! :D

description: Welcome to Homeless Technology, where we navigate the digital wilderness with the finesse of a tech-savvy hobo! Join us as we embark on a journey through the pixelated streets of gaming and the tangled wires of tech, all while embracing the struggles of surviving in a world where Wi-Fi signals are as elusive as spare change. From makeshift gaming rigs to ingenious hacks for charging devices without a power outlet in sight, we're here to prove that even without a permanent address, you can still pwn the digital realm like a boss. So grab your cardboard box, charge up your smartphone (borrowed charger optional), and let's dive headfirst into the chaotic adventure of homelessness meets high-tech hilarity!

description:
I feature videos from mostly Northeast Maryland and Southern Pennsylvania! 99% of these videos are ones that I have recorded while Railfanning!

The Ultimate Railfanner is now on Facebook!
https://www.facebook.com/pages/UltimateRailfanner-Videos/162002140510490#

Camera Equipment:
Canon Vixia HG20 HDD Camcorder, Canon EOS 60D, Canon EOS Rebel XS, Canon EFS 18-135mm, Canon 75-300mm, Canon EFS 18-55mm, Canon 50m f/1.8.

All of my videos are shot in 1080p 60fps video. When edited and uploaded, fps is decreased to 30fps to maintain 1080p since YouTube cannot handle 60fps. When my videos are in 720p, they are uploaded in 60fps, but YouTube still takes away the effect.

If you have any suggestions to any of my future videos, such as new angles, new locations, etc., please message me privately at ultimaterailfanner@gmail.com or comment on this video.

Have a nice day/night, and I hope you enjoy my videos!


-Nick (Owner)

Professionals, enthusiasts, and newcomers alike are welcome to experience our products first-hand, and our warm, knowledgeable and professional staff is here to provide expert information and friendly service and to ensure the ultimate in customer satisfaction.

description:
I started out with an Atari 2600 from a second-hand shop somewhere around 35 years ago and I'm still just as crazy about games as I was back then.

I left the genetics program at University of Alberta after my first year, looking to find something other than a life surrounded by windowless concrete walls. I wound up finding a job and started writing PC game reviews on the side, first for a small independent site and eventually writing PC and console reviews for EGM and Incite. Those gigs landed me a job at a newspaper - one that I would only agree to take if they allowed me to do a weekly games column.

That was 16 years ago, and - though I left the paper to do other things - I'm still doing the column.

I'm totally open to taking suggestions, so if you've got a game you think I'd love let me know.

description:
After gaining renown on the French indie scene, the band’s fame increased through their first albums’ tours. The fame became international with the amazing success of the track LET'S GO in France and abroad and a tremendous interest from North and South American audiences. 
Some 280 million streams later, the band comes back to introduce a 6th album.
For this chapter, the band wanted to keep its independence and free itself from all framework, even refusing the ease of their successful formulas. In the studio they built themselves (that is to say their desire for autonomy!), the musicians tried new artistic approaches, with the desire to rediscover the excitement and wonder of their beginnings. For nearly 3 years, they explored, composed and recorded, through each member’s artistic affinities. And for the1st time in their career, they called on an outside director, the young English prodigy Ash Workman (who produced some of the best records of Metronomy and Christine and the Queens)

description:
The first television station in the state of Ohio, and the most awarded in Cleveland, News 5 Cleveland (WEWS) is an ABC affiliate owned by Scripps.

We take a different approach. Too often in TV news reporting, viewers don’t know what happened after the initial story, how the victims or communities coped in the days and weeks after, or what resolutions to issues were ever reached. Our "We Follow Through" promise means that News 5 not only shows up when news breaks but comes back again and again with in-depth reporting. News 5’s entire team of anchors, reporters, investigators, and photographers are part of this effort, and the style of storytelling extends to all platforms.

In addition to our station in Cleveland, we have bureaus in Akron and Columbus. We are media partners with the Akron Beacon Journal, Marshall Project Cleveland, and Ohio Capital Journal, and we're the official TV partners of the Browns.

description:
Speedncontrol features videos from the motorsport hobby of Mark West.  I first began driving in High Performance Driving Events in late 2008 and have been hooked ever since.  After HPDE's for a couple of years I moved on to NASA Time Trials, and then NASA Racing (wheel to wheel).  

My track cars have included a Ferrari, Noble M400, 2 daily driver Nissan GT-R's, a dedicated Nissan GT-R race car and a Porsche GT3.  There's nothing quite like the exhilaration of driving a car the way it's meant to be driven on a dedicated road course.  I hope you enjoy the videos and consider joining us out there someday!

After winning the NASA Regional Championships in 2015, I retired from racing and recently sold the Liberty GT-R race car.  Many good memories for sure, but it's time to move on to new, eternal priorities.  Thank God for protection, and patience as I worked through this phase of my life.

Polizei 144 — the world's infamous outlaw racing team — was founded in 2002 by Alex Roy, who has set or broken more underground endurance driving records than anyone alive. Easily recognized by their customizable police motojackets and car liveries, Polizei 144 dominated races and rallies like the Gumball 3000 and Bullrun from 2003 to 2007, after which Roy led the effort that shattered the Cannonball Run record by over an hour.

Total time from New York to LA? 31 hours, 4 minutes.

The Cannonball record is depicted in Roy's book The Driver, and the documentary 32 Hours, 7 Minutes.

As of 2017, Polizei 144 has set or broken dozens more driving records, only 8 of which are currently public, and will be revealed when it becomes legally possible to do so.

description:
This channel is all about the nations I've visited and nations I plan to visit.   I've been to 135 nations (at least 4 days) including the 7th Continent. There is more sovereign nations I am hoping and praying to be able to see.  I am so grateful to God  who has given me the opportunities to travel and see the world.  

These global travel experiences have given me better perspectives on culture, customs and traditions of other nations and about humanity, in general.  I still have so much things to see and learn and I keep myself open to these future opportunities.  

Travel experiences are priceless and will always remain fresh in my mind - until my last breath.  It has a long-lasting value than any material thing. If you have a passion to see the world, please do so and start in a small scale.   

I'm  a Christian.My guiding verse when traveling is Joshua 1:9"Be strong and courageous, do not be discouraged nor dismayed, for I'm with you everywhere you go."
